In this article, Vice President Kamala Harris speaks at the Carole Hoefener Center in Charlotte, North Carolina about the importance of high-speed Internet access. She discusses the Affordable Connectivity Program, which provides working families with discounts on their Internet bills and offers a one-time discount for purchasing devices like laptops or tablets. Harris highlights the impact of the program, such as allowing students to study at home and giving families access to healthcare through telehealth services. She emphasizes the need for everyone to have affordable Internet access and calls on the audience to spread the word about the program and help people fill out applications. Harris also mentions other initiatives aimed at lowering costs for working families, such as the expansion of the Child Tax Credit and efforts to lower the price of prescription drugs and healthcare. She concludes by thanking the audience for their support and encouraging continued efforts to connect people to a better future.